## 🐛 Bug Report

Lib version: 4.3.0

## Steps To Reproduce

When using the addtable function to create multiple tables on a single sheet and then using the mergecells function to merge cells within the created tables, opening the resulting Excel file in Microsoft Excel generates a warning that the file is corrupted.

<br>

<img width="262" alt="스크린샷 2023-04-03 오후 11 21 09" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/115525602/229686504-0adc9cab-5ebc-4311-9ffb-22a0f37e0b48.png">

<Br>

<!-- The exact steps required to reproduce the issue, ideally with a code example -->

```javascript
  worksheet.addTable({
      name: `a${randomUUID().slice(0, 8).replace(/-/g, "")}`,
      ref,
      style: {
        theme: "TableStyleLight1",
      },
      columns,
      rows,
    });
  const targetCol = `A${targetRowIdx}:B${targetRowIdx}`;
  worksheet.mergeCells(targetCol);
```

- If the mergecells code is commented out, the file can be opened normally.

